HEADWORD: Moniliales
<hw>Mo*nil`i*a"les</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. L. <ets>monile</ets> necklace, -- because the conidia are produced
in chains.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The largest of the three orders
into which the Fungi Imperfecti are divided, including various
forms.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

